00:48:28,697 --> 00:48:31,116
to make her write such a letter
before killing herself?

519
00:48:31,199 --> 00:48:33,285
What wicked act
won't she forget even in death?

520
00:48:33,368 --> 00:48:36,747
Ladies, I feel like
we might be getting too worked up--

521
00:48:36,830 --> 00:48:37,956
Answer me!

522
00:48:39,249 --> 00:48:41,418
I told you last time, didn't I?

523
00:48:41,501 --> 00:48:44,463
There's a whole line of people
who'd send me that kind of letter.

524
00:48:45,047 --> 00:48:49,009
And I'll do whatever it takes
to find those people and ruin them.

525
00:49:05,150 --> 00:49:08,362
How did you know that the textbook
would be in the trash, Su-in?

526
00:49:09,321 --> 00:49:15,494
I saw Dong-seok's erasers
and pencils in there last time.

527
00:49:16,870 --> 00:49:18,121
Did you see who did it?

528
00:49:19,164 --> 00:49:20,540
Yu-bin.

529
00:49:27,714 --> 00:49:29,633
Thank you for being honest, Su-in.

530
00:49:29,716 --> 00:49:31,468
Okay guys, let's start class now.

531
00:49:31,551 --> 00:49:33,595
-Okay.
-Dong-seok, take this.

532
00:49:33,679 --> 00:49:35,806
All right, open up Science 1062.

533
00:49:45,315 --> 00:49:47,109
No matter how much I think about it…

534
00:49:48,652 --> 00:49:50,779
What in the world is going on?

535
00:49:50,862 --> 00:49:52,698
And what's with that letter?

536
00:49:52,781 --> 00:49:53,824
I know.

537
00:49:53,907 --> 00:49:57,327
Does that mean
this whole thing was Chun-hui's idea?

538
00:50:00,330 --> 00:50:02,833
Su-in's mom, is there anything you know?

539
00:50:03,959 --> 00:50:07,671
No, I don't know anything at all.

540
00:50:09,047 --> 00:50:12,175
Goodness. I have plans
and I think I'm running late.

541
00:50:12,259 --> 00:50:14,261
-I'll get going.
-All right.

542
00:50:51,256 --> 00:50:52,966
SANGWE BIG MART

543
00:51:11,693 --> 00:51:14,488
-Yun-ju, you have to switch shifts now.
-Okay.

544
00:51:14,571 --> 00:51:16,198
Get up. I'll finish up.

545
00:51:22,204 --> 00:51:23,538
Hello.

546
00:51:28,376 --> 00:51:29,753
Hey, what's wrong?

547
00:51:29,836 --> 00:51:32,380
Wait a minute, please.

548
00:51:32,464 --> 00:51:33,840
I'm so sorry.

549
00:51:44,643 --> 00:51:47,395
Excuse me. I'm in a rush.

550
00:51:47,479 --> 00:51:49,815
Just a minute, please.

551
00:51:49,898 --> 00:51:51,316
I'm so sorry.

552
00:51:53,693 --> 00:51:55,320
Goodness.

553
00:51:55,403 --> 00:51:56,696
I'm busy.

554
00:52:00,534 --> 00:52:01,535
Bye.

555
00:52:04,955 --> 00:52:06,832
-Sorry about that.
-Goodness.

556
00:52:32,107 --> 00:52:34,192
If you ever lock the door again,

557
00:52:35,819 --> 00:52:37,821
I'll lock you up forever.

558
00:52:38,905 --> 00:52:40,490
What's going on?

559
00:52:41,241 --> 00:52:44,953
Jul-pin was fooling around
and broke a vase.

560
00:52:46,454 --> 00:52:48,456
We can just sweep it up.

561
00:52:48,540 --> 00:52:51,251
I don't think Jul-pin feels
that he's done anything wrong.

562
00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:57,591
Isn't building character
the most important thing?

563
00:52:58,341 --> 00:52:59,634
Isn't that right, Jul-pin?

564
00:53:22,449 --> 00:53:24,451
If you ever lock the door again,

565
00:53:25,827 --> 00:53:28,163
I'll lock you up forever.

566
00:54:03,114 --> 00:54:07,035
The cup resembled the one we received.

567
00:54:07,118 --> 00:54:09,162
The only kids that live on the floors
above the security camera

568
00:54:09,245 --> 00:54:11,456
that went to Sangwe Kindergarten
are Jul-pin and Henry.

569
00:54:11,539 --> 00:54:15,043
I'm just asking you
to check if you have the cup or not.

570
00:54:16,836 --> 00:54:18,463
Why aren't you sleeping?

571
00:54:18,546 --> 00:54:22,133
Oh, I just couldn't fall asleep.

572
00:54:41,736 --> 00:54:43,738
YU-BIN'S MOM

573
00:55:38,793 --> 00:55:44,299
CHUN-HUI, HOW DID WE END UP LIKE THIS?

574
00:55:44,382 --> 00:55:48,011
LOUIS BENUEL:
SEO JIN-HA'S FUNERAL

575
00:55:48,094 --> 00:55:49,262
YU-BIN'S MOM

576
00:56:09,783 --> 00:56:11,201
-Eun-pyo.
-Yes?

577
00:56:12,744 --> 00:56:13,953
Why aren't you going in?

578
00:56:14,537 --> 00:56:16,790
Right. Let's head inside.

579
00:56:31,721 --> 00:56:33,014
LEE EUN-PYO

580
00:57:17,225 --> 00:57:20,353
You smell like a mom, ma'am.

581
00:57:21,563 --> 00:57:23,982
I really like you.

582
00:57:26,276 --> 00:57:27,777
Goodness.

583
00:57:27,861 --> 00:57:30,864
How is it possible
that I'm seeing you again like this?

584
00:57:31,781 --> 00:57:33,032
Eun-pyo.

585
00:57:42,584 --> 00:57:44,085
She's so pretty.

586
00:57:45,670 --> 00:57:47,380
Goodness.

587
00:58:47,774 --> 00:58:49,776
MAY SHE REST IN PEACE

588
00:58:57,200 --> 00:58:58,535
Eun-pyo.

589
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:06,459
It's been a while.

590
00:59:06,543 --> 00:59:08,211
Thank you for coming.

591
00:59:27,730 --> 00:59:28,982
Eun-pyo, come over here.

592
00:59:30,483 --> 00:59:31,693
You too.

593
00:59:38,199 --> 00:59:39,492
Sit here.

594
00:59:58,803 --> 01:00:01,180
Back inside the funeral hall,

595
01:00:01,264 --> 01:00:04,642
did you see how Dong-seok's mother
and Henry's father looked at each other?

596
01:00:04,726 --> 01:00:06,019
No, why?

597
01:00:06,102 --> 01:00:07,729
It was strange.

598
01:00:07,812 --> 01:00:10,148
As if they were super uncomfortable
with each other.

599
01:00:10,648 --> 01:00:12,358
-They looked uncomfortable?
-Yes.

600
01:00:12,442 --> 01:00:15,028
Then maybe they didn't have an affair.

601
01:00:15,111 --> 01:00:17,488
No, I think they
definitely did have an affair.

602
01:00:18,156 --> 01:00:21,492
But I think there's
something else with Chun-hui.

603
01:00:21,576 --> 01:00:23,911
Gosh, the whole thing is a mess.

604
01:00:23,995 --> 01:00:25,913
Jeez, I don't even know anymore.

605
01:00:25,997 --> 01:00:27,707
I just feel bad for the deceased.

606
01:00:28,750 --> 01:00:30,585
What is Henry going to do without a mom?

607
01:00:30,668 --> 01:00:32,879
Let's go in. It's cold.

608
01:00:32,962 --> 01:00:34,672
-You're cold?
-Yes.

609
01:00:34,756 --> 01:00:36,966
I thought I brought it. That's strange.

610
01:00:47,852 --> 01:00:49,395
It's kind of windy.

611
01:00:54,442 --> 01:00:56,444
I'll head home now.

612
01:00:56,527 --> 01:00:57,904
You haven't eaten yet.

613
01:00:58,529 --> 01:01:01,032
My mom's looking after the boys,
so I need to get back.

614
01:01:01,115 --> 01:01:02,825
-Bye.
-Bye.

615
01:01:02,909 --> 01:01:03,910
Get home safe.

616
01:01:09,666 --> 01:01:13,044
-Sir, can I talk to you for a moment?
-When did you get here?

617
01:01:25,723 --> 01:01:28,518
I knew something was off.

618
01:01:29,143 --> 01:01:31,312
She's not one to just die like that.

619
01:01:31,396 --> 01:01:35,233
How dare you come here
and act like you care?

620
01:01:35,316 --> 01:01:36,526
You little…

621
01:01:36,609 --> 01:01:37,735
You killed her.

622
01:01:37,819 --> 01:01:38,695
You killed her!

623
01:01:38,778 --> 01:01:42,699
Bring her back!

624
01:01:43,449 --> 01:01:45,201
You killed her!

625
01:01:45,284 --> 01:01:46,786
What are you doing?

626
01:01:47,787 --> 01:01:50,623
She didn't kill your daughter.

627
01:01:50,707 --> 01:01:53,000
-What do you know?
-I'm…

628
01:01:54,836 --> 01:01:56,629
her husband.

629
01:01:58,089 --> 01:01:59,132
What is he saying?

630
01:01:59,799 --> 01:02:00,758
Let's go.

631
01:02:09,851 --> 01:02:11,144
Goodness.

632
01:02:38,129 --> 01:02:39,422
Are you dumb?

633
01:02:42,550 --> 01:02:44,594
Why would you stand there
and let her hit you?

634
01:02:48,097 --> 01:02:50,391
Why couldn't you tell her she was wrong?

635
01:02:52,935 --> 01:02:56,397
People are more suspicious of you
because you won't stand up for yourself.

636
01:03:16,209 --> 01:03:17,460
It's true…

637
01:03:19,670 --> 01:03:23,841
that I went out with Louis.

638
01:03:25,384 --> 01:03:28,012
But he dumped me

639
01:03:29,555 --> 01:03:31,265
because Jin-ha showed up.

640
01:03:35,603 --> 01:03:37,772
As soon as that happened,

641
01:03:39,690 --> 01:03:41,734
he never even looked back.

642
01:03:46,072 --> 01:03:47,615
It was always like that.

643
01:03:49,700 --> 01:03:51,077
Jin-ha would always…

644
01:03:53,120 --> 01:03:55,248
take away everything

645
01:03:57,959 --> 01:03:59,836
that meant a lot to me.

646
01:04:03,673 --> 01:04:05,967
But more than being dumped,

647
01:04:08,344 --> 01:04:10,513
I couldn't stand the fact that

648
01:04:11,848 --> 01:04:13,975
she took him away from me.

649
01:04:19,355 --> 01:04:20,523
Yes.

650
01:04:23,192 --> 01:04:25,111
I have a miserable life.

651
01:04:27,321 --> 01:04:29,615
You might ask why I'm so discontent

652
01:04:31,659 --> 01:04:34,495
when I have a husband and children.

653
01:04:36,414 --> 01:04:37,790
But…

654
01:04:40,501 --> 01:04:42,003
more than anything,

655
01:04:43,838 --> 01:04:45,214
for all of my life,

656
01:04:46,674 --> 01:04:49,594
all I wanted was to be a daughter

657
01:04:51,762 --> 01:04:53,931
that my mom could be proud of.

658
01:04:56,809 --> 01:04:57,935
So…

659
01:04:59,770 --> 01:05:02,607
I did everything I could
to work towards that.

660
01:05:07,194 --> 01:05:09,447
Then I met Jin-ha again.

661
01:05:11,449 --> 01:05:13,784
The one who makes me
feel utterly pathetic.

662
01:05:18,789 --> 01:05:21,375
I wanted to know
despite how much time had passed.

663
01:05:23,044 --> 01:05:24,795
I wanted to know why he dumped me.

664
01:05:27,715 --> 01:05:30,843
If being curious about that
is enough to say I was having an affair,

665
01:05:33,179 --> 01:05:35,222
then so be it.

666
01:05:38,851 --> 01:05:41,103
But my broken pride

667
01:05:42,980 --> 01:05:44,857
kept telling me to do that.

668
01:05:51,197 --> 01:05:52,448
I'm sorry.

669
01:06:12,969 --> 01:06:14,512
But you know what?

670
01:06:17,974 --> 01:06:21,102
You're still the most impressive thing
I've ever laid my eyes on.

671
01:06:25,898 --> 01:06:27,149
Also…

672
01:06:28,317 --> 01:06:30,152
I was never around to help…

673
01:06:32,279 --> 01:06:34,031
while you were studying.

674
01:06:39,537 --> 01:06:41,664
I've always felt bad about that.

675
01:06:45,543 --> 01:06:46,961
Of course, I know.

676
01:06:48,087 --> 01:06:52,550
I know you could be
doing greater things in life.

677
01:07:11,193 --> 01:07:12,778
Did you hear?

678
01:07:13,404 --> 01:07:16,991
One of the boys from Class Three
molested one of the girls.

679
01:07:17,074 --> 01:07:18,659
-Oh, my gosh.
-Who was it?

680
01:07:19,368 --> 01:07:20,619
From what I hear…

681
01:07:55,863 --> 01:07:58,866
Did you know?
They were molested by Dong-seok.

682
01:07:58,949 --> 01:08:01,660
My daughter is
the most important thing to me.

683
01:08:01,744 --> 01:08:05,206
How are my son and daughter
doing these days?

684
01:08:05,289 --> 01:08:07,541
I just want to focus on
raising my kids properly.

685
01:08:07,625 --> 01:08:11,170
Even if you open up to a friend,
they're still strangers in the end.

686
01:08:11,253 --> 01:08:14,632
I want my dad to be happy,

687
01:08:15,257 --> 01:08:18,385
but I also don't want my mom to be sad.

688
01:08:18,469 --> 01:08:20,346
How are you any different
from those women right now?

689
01:08:20,429 --> 01:08:22,807
You should be out there telling them
to stop spreading all that nonsense!

690
01:08:23,390 --> 01:08:26,852
But what I want is for your family
to leave this community entirely.

691
01:08:26,936 --> 01:08:29,271
I don't care how messy things get.

692
01:08:29,855 --> 01:08:32,858
I'm going to make sure that my boy
comes out of this unscathed.

693
01:08:34,026 --> 01:08:39,031
